'From Squeak3.1alpha of 5 February 2001 [latest update: #4100] on 29 May 2001 at 10:00:34 am'!"Change Set:		lessGrowingDate:			29 May 2001Author:			Bob ArningPerhaps a bit controversial, but increasing the initial size of a MethodDictionary will decrease the number of times it needs to grow as methods are added. Can save on the order of 15 to 20% on the time required to filein a change set."!!MethodDictionary class methodsFor: 'instance creation' stamp: 'RAA 5/29/2001 09:53'!new	"change the default size to be a bit bigger to help reduce the number of #grows while filing in"	^self new: 16! !